<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-11-27T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-11-27T16:00:00-05:00" n="185" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d185">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">860p.512 Residence/10: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in Latvia</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Sussdorff</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-11-27T16:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">November 27,
                                        1928—4 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>69. Your 95, November 22, 10 a.m. Request exemption from tax for American
                            nationals under paragraph 2, Article 1, of the treaty concluded April
                            20, 1928, which accords national treatment in matters of internal
                            charges or taxes.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>